<li id="cite_note-42"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news" id="CITEREFChris_Garcia">Chris Garcia (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2006-12-06"><a href="/wiki/2006" title="2006">2006</a>-<a href="/wiki/December_6" title="December 6">12-06</a></span>). <a href="http://www.statesman.com/search/content/shared/movies/stories/2006/12/history.html" class="external text" title="http://www.statesman.com/search/content/shared/movies/stories/2006/12/history.html" rel="nofollow">"'Apocalypto' is an insult to Maya culture, one expert says"</a>. <a href="/wiki/American-Statesman" title="American-Statesman" class="mw-redirect">American-Statesman</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.statesman.com/search/content/shared/movies/stories/2006/12/history.html" class="external free" title="http://www.statesman.com/search/content/shared/movies/stories/2006/12/history.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.statesman.com/search/content/shared/movies/stories/2006/12/history.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=%27Apocalypto%27+is+an+insult+to+Maya+culture%2C+one+expert+says&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Chris+Garcia&amp;rft.au=Chris+Garcia&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2006-12-06%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BAmerican-Statesman%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.statesman.com%2Fsearch%2Fcontent%2Fshared%2Fmovies%2Fstories%2F2006%2F12%2Fhistory.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Apocalypto"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-43"><b><a href="#cite_ref-43" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.globalheritagefund.org/apocalypto.html" class="external text" title="http://www.globalheritagefund.org/apocalypto.html" rel="nofollow">" "globalheritagefund.org"</a><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.globalheritagefund.org/apocalypto.html" class="external free" title="http://www.globalheritagefund.org/apocalypto.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.globalheritagefund.org/apocalypto.html</a>"</span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-12-04</span>.  "About 25 members of the Maya community in Los Angeles were invited to an advance screening of Gibson's film last week. Two of those who attended came away impressed, but added that they too wished Gibson had shown more of the Maya civilization. "It was a great action film that kept me on the edge of my seat," said Sara Zapata Mijares, president and founder of Federacion de Clubes Yucatecos-USA. "I think it should have had a little bit more of the culture," such as the pyramids. "It could have shown a little more why these buildings were built."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=globalheritagefund.org&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalheritagefund.org%2Fapocalypto.html%22&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Apocalypto"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-44"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44" title="">^</a></b> Translation from the original in Spanish: "La mala noticia es que esta interpretación histórica tiene alguna dosis de realidad […]. Los personajes de Mel Gibson se parecen más a los mayas de los murales de Bonampak que a los que aparecen en los libros de la SEP" —<i><a href="/wiki/Reforma" title="Reforma">Reforma</a></i>, "Nacionalismo de piel delgada", 4 February 2007.</li>
